hwIASSigtranObjects.name: hwIASSigtranObjects

revisions.description: V1.23, modify the value range of hwL2uaLinkMaxInStreamNum,hwL2uaLinkMaxOutStreamNum in hwL2uaLinkMngtTable

V1.23, modify the value range of hwL2uaLinkActiveStandbyFlag,hwL2uaLinkUsedOutStreamNum,hwL2uaLinkUsedInStreamNum, hwL2uaLinkCongestState,hwL2uaLinkMaintainOper,hwL2uaLinkLockStatus in hwL2uaLinkMngtTable
V1.22, delete the default value of hwMifSctpCfgParaSendChecksum and hwMifSctpCfgParaRecvChecksum
V1.20, modified the type and range of the hwSctpAssocLocalRwnd and hwSctpAssocRemoteRwnd
V1.15, add trap notification and correct compile error
V1.14, add hwL2uaLinkLocalIpDynamicIPName to support DHCP
V1.13, add hwSctpGlobalParaTable to SCTP global parameters configuration

hwIASSigtranObjects.contactinfo: Huawei Industrial Base Bantian, Longgang Shenzhen 518129 People's Republic of China Website: http://www.huawei.com Email: support@huawei.com
hwIASSigtranObjects.description: This MIB module defines MIB objects which provides SIGTRAN management.

hwL2uaLinkSetMngtTable.name: hwL2uaLinkSetMngtTable
hwL2uaLinkSetMngtTable.description: This table is used to config L2UA linkset. The index of this table is hwL2uaLinkSetNo.

hwL2uaLinkSetMngtEntry.name: hwL2uaLinkSetMngtEntry
hwL2uaLinkSetMngtEntry.description: This table is used to config L2UA linkset. The index of this entry is hwL2uaLinkSetNo.

hwL2uaLinkSetProtocolType.name: hwL2uaLinkSetProtocolType
hwL2uaLinkSetProtocolType.description: Protocol type. Options: 1. iua(1) -indicates that the Protocol type is IUA 2. m2ua(2) -indicates that that the Protocol type is M2UA 3. v5ua(5) -indicates that that the Protocol type is V5UA(currently, only IUA is supported.)

hwL2uaLinkSetPendingTime.name: hwL2uaLinkSetPendingTime
hwL2uaLinkSetPendingTime.description: The pending time of the link set (the last active link in the link set switches to another state. During the pending time length, if no link in the link set switches to the active state, the link set enters the inactive or down state.). Default: 4 Unit: second

hwL2uaLinkSetTrafficMode.name: hwL2uaLinkSetTrafficMode
hwL2uaLinkSetTrafficMode.description: The working mode of the link set. Options: 1. override(1) -indicates that the working mode of the link set is override 2. loadshare(2) -indicates that the working mode of the link set is loadshare

hwL2uaLinkSetCSMode.name: hwL2uaLinkSetCSMode
hwL2uaLinkSetCSMode.description: C/S mode of the link set. Options: 1. client(1) -indicates that the C/S mode of the link set is Client 2. server(2) -indicates that the C/S mode of the link set is Server Default: 2

hwL2uaLinkSetIIDType.name: hwL2uaLinkSetIIDType
hwL2uaLinkSetIIDType.description: Type of the interface ID. Options: 1. integer(1) -integer 2. text(2) -text

hwL2uaLinkSetLinkNum.name: hwL2uaLinkSetLinkNum
hwL2uaLinkSetLinkNum.description: The number of links in the link set

hwL2uaLinkSetOperState.name: hwL2uaLinkSetOperState
hwL2uaLinkSetOperState.description: Status of the link set. Options: 1. down(1) -indicates that the Status of the link set is down 2. inactive(2) -indicates that the Status of the link set is inactive 3. active(3) -indicates that the Status of the link set is active 4. pending(4) -indicates that the Status of the link set is pending

hwL2uaLinkSetMgId.name: hwL2uaLinkSetMgId
hwL2uaLinkSetMgId.description: MG interface ID. -1 means this parameter is not configured.

hwL2uaLinkSetIidMap.name: hwL2uaLinkSetIidMap
hwL2uaLinkSetIidMap.description: InterfaceID generation mode. 1:generated by user input,use format:interfaceID 2:generated automatically,use format:ffsspp, ff-shelf number,ss-slot number, pp-port number, decimal number 3:generated automatically,use format:rrrrfffffssssspppppppxxxxxxxxxxx ,rrrr-rack, fffff-shelf number,sssss-slot number, ppppppp-port number,xxxxxxxxxxx-reserved,binary number 4:generated automatically,FT text format:prefix+ff/ss/pp, ff-shelf number,ss-slot number, pp-port number, text 5:generated by user input,use format:braprefix+interfaceID+brasuffix or praprefix+interfaceID+prasuffix, the length of praprefix+interfaceID+prasuffix must be shorter than 31 Default:1

hwL2uaLinkSetJointlyWork.name: hwL2uaLinkSetJointlyWork
hwL2uaLinkSetJointlyWork.description: IUA link joint work with MGC. Options: 1.enable(1) -support IUA Link joint work with MGC 2.disable(2) -not support IUA Link joint work with MGC It must config together with hwL2uaLinkSetMgId.

hwL2uaLinkSetIidPrefix.name: hwL2uaLinkSetIidPrefix
hwL2uaLinkSetIidPrefix.description: Indicates the prefix of IID.The prefix is not allowed to contain the character:';'':'','

hwL2uaLinkSetIidBraPrefix.name: hwL2uaLinkSetIidBraPrefix
hwL2uaLinkSetIidBraPrefix.description: Indicates the bra prefix of IID.The prefix is not allowed to contain the character:';'':'','

hwL2uaLinkSetIidBraSuffix.name: hwL2uaLinkSetIidBraSuffix
hwL2uaLinkSetIidBraSuffix.description: Indicates the bra suffix of IID.The suffix is not allowed to contain the character:';'':'','

hwL2uaLinkSetIidPraPrefix.name: hwL2uaLinkSetIidPraPrefix
hwL2uaLinkSetIidPraPrefix.description: Indicates the pra prefix of IID.The prefix is not allowed to contain the character:';'':'','

hwL2uaLinkSetIidPrasuffix.name: hwL2uaLinkSetIidPrasuffix
hwL2uaLinkSetIidPrasuffix.description: Indicates the pra suffix of IID.The suffix is not allowed to contain the character:';'':'','

hwL2uaLinkMngtTable.name: hwL2uaLinkMngtTable
hwL2uaLinkMngtTable.description: This table is used to config L2UA link. The index of this table is hwL2uaLinkNo.

hwL2uaLinkMngtEntry.name: hwL2uaLinkMngtEntry
hwL2uaLinkMngtEntry.description: This table is used to config L2UA link. The index of this entry is hwL2uaLinkNo.

hwL2uaLinkMaxInStreamNum.name: hwL2uaLinkMaxInStreamNum
hwL2uaLinkMaxInStreamNum.description: Maximum number of inbound streams. -1 means the IUA link is configurated with DHCP but the vlan IP isn't gained by DHCP.

hwL2uaLinkMaxOutStreamNum.name: hwL2uaLinkMaxOutStreamNum
hwL2uaLinkMaxOutStreamNum.description: Maximum number of outbound streams. -1 means the IUA link is configurated with DHCP but the vlan IP isn't gained by DHCP.

hwL2uaLinkActiveStandbyFlag.name: hwL2uaLinkActiveStandbyFlag
hwL2uaLinkActiveStandbyFlag.description: Active and standby flag. Options: 1. active(1)-indicates that the Active and standby flag is active 2. standby(2)-indicates that the Active and standby flag is standby 3. null(-1)-indicates that the Active and standby flag is invalid Display -1 when the vlanid can't get Local IP in dhcp mode.

hwL2uaLinkLockFlag.name: hwL2uaLinkLockFlag
hwL2uaLinkLockFlag.description: IUA Link maintenance lock flag. Options: 1. lock(1)-indicates that the IUA Link maintenance lock flag is active 2. unlock(2)-indicates that the IUA Link maintenance lock flag is standby

hwL2uaLinkUsedInStreamNum.name: hwL2uaLinkUsedInStreamNum
hwL2uaLinkUsedInStreamNum.description: Number of inbound streams used currently -1 indicates that the number is invalid

hwL2uaLinkUsedOutStreamNum.name: hwL2uaLinkUsedOutStreamNum
hwL2uaLinkUsedOutStreamNum.description: Number of outbound streams used currently -1 indicates that the number is invalid

hwL2uaLinkSctpAssocId.name: hwL2uaLinkSctpAssocId
hwL2uaLinkSctpAssocId.description: SCTP association ID that the L2UA link corresponds to -1 means there is no SCTP association.

hwL2uaLinkOperState.name: hwL2uaLinkOperState
hwL2uaLinkOperState.description: Link status. Options: 1. unestablish(1)-indicates that the Link status is active 2. establish(2)-indicates that the Link status is standby 3. inactive(3)-indicates that the Link status is inactive 4. active(4)-indicates that the Link status is active

hwL2uaLinkCongestState.name: hwL2uaLinkCongestState
hwL2uaLinkCongestState.description: Congestion state. Options: 1. uncongest(1) -not congested 2. congest(2) -congested 3. null(-1) -null Display -1 when the vlanid can't get Local IP in dhcp mode.

hwL2uaLinkMaintainOper.name: hwL2uaLinkMaintainOper
hwL2uaLinkMaintainOper.description: Link maintenance operation. Options: 1. lock(1) -indicates that the link maintenance operation is Lock 2. unlock(2) -indicates that the link maintenance operation is Unlock 3. reset(3) -indicates that the link status is Reset 4. null(-1) -indicates that the link maintenance operation is invalid

hwL2uaLinkWithMedGwyCtrlIdx.name: hwL2uaLinkWithMedGwyCtrlIdx
hwL2uaLinkWithMedGwyCtrlIdx.description: Config IUA Link jiont work with witch MGC. 0: Primary MGC. 1: Secondary MGC. -1 means this parameter is not configed.

hwL2uaLinkPriority.name: hwL2uaLinkPriority
hwL2uaLinkPriority.description: Is available when the working mode of the link set is Load-share. In Over ride mode, this parameter can be read, but no use. Default:0

hwL2uaLinkLockStatus.name: hwL2uaLinkLockStatus
hwL2uaLinkLockStatus.description: IUA Link current Lock State: Options: 1. unlock(1)-indicates that the Current IUA Link not locked 2. servicelock(2)-indicates that the Current IUA Link was locked for joint work with MGC 3. maintenancelock(3)-indicates that the Current IUA Link was locked by maintenance operation Adminlock have pripority over autolock. 4. display -1 when the vlanid can't get Local IP in dhcp mode.

hwL2uaLinkLocalIpaddrDhcpClientIndex.name: hwL2uaLinkLocalIpaddrDhcpClientIndex
hwL2uaLinkLocalIpaddrDhcpClientIndex.description: Dhcp L2ua vlan id. The valid value is 1..4093,if the value is -1, the static signal ip will be used.

hwSctpAssocStatTable.name: hwSctpAssocStatTable
hwSctpAssocStatTable.description: This table is used to query statistic of a SCTP association. The index of this table is hwSctpAssocStatAssocId.

hwSctpAssocStatEntry.name: hwSctpAssocStatEntry
hwSctpAssocStatEntry.description: This table is used to query statistic of a SCTP association. The index of this entry is hwSctpAssocStatAssocId.

hwSctpAssocStatAssocId.name: hwSctpAssocStatAssocId
hwSctpAssocStatAssocId.description: SCTP association ID Constructed by Protocol-Type, MGC-index/Proxy-index, IUA-Link-ID/H248-Interface-ID/SIP-Interface-ID; Format:xyzzzzzz(Hex) a) x for Protocol-Type: IUA(0),H.248(1),SIP(2); b) y for MGC-index/Proxy-index: if x is IUA(0), y fixed to 0; if x is H.248(1), y for MGC index; if x is SIP(2), y for Proxy index; c) z for IUA-Link-ID/H248-Interface-ID/SIP-Interface-ID: if x is IUA(0), zzzzzz for IUA LinkNo; if x is H.248(1), zzzzzz for H248 interface ID; if x is SIP(2), zzzzzz for SIP interface ID;

hwSctpAssocStatT1Expired.name: hwSctpAssocStatT1Expired
hwSctpAssocStatT1Expired.description: The expired times of the T1 timer

hwSctpAssocStatT2Expired.name: hwSctpAssocStatT2Expired
hwSctpAssocStatT2Expired.description: The expired times of the T2 timer

hwSctpAssocStatRetransChunks.name: hwSctpAssocStatRetransChunks
hwSctpAssocStatRetransChunks.description: The number of retransmitted data chunks

hwSctpAssocStatSendDataChunks.name: hwSctpAssocStatSendDataChunks
hwSctpAssocStatSendDataChunks.description: The number of transmitted data chunks.

hwSctpAssocStatRevDataChunks.name: hwSctpAssocStatRevDataChunks
hwSctpAssocStatRevDataChunks.description: The number of received data chunks

hwSctpAssocStatRecPackets.name: hwSctpAssocStatRecPackets
hwSctpAssocStatRecPackets.description: The number of received SCTP packets

hwSctpAssocStatRecErrPackets.name: hwSctpAssocStatRecErrPackets
hwSctpAssocStatRecErrPackets.description: The number of received error SCTP packets

hwSctpAssocStatOperStatus.name: hwSctpAssocStatOperStatus
hwSctpAssocStatOperStatus.description: Clearing the statistics of the associations. Options: 1. clear(1) -clear

hwSctpAssocStatSentSctpPackets.name: hwSctpAssocStatSentSctpPackets
hwSctpAssocStatSentSctpPackets.description: The number of the transmitted SCTP packets

hwSctpGlobalStatAssocActEstab.name: hwSctpGlobalStatAssocActEstab
hwSctpGlobalStatAssocActEstab.description: The number of associations initiated by the local end

hwSctpGlobalStatAssocPassiveEstab.name: hwSctpGlobalStatAssocPassiveEstab
hwSctpGlobalStatAssocPassiveEstab.description: The number of associations initiated by the remote end

hwSctpGlobalStatAssocActFail.name: hwSctpGlobalStatAssocActFail
hwSctpGlobalStatAssocActFail.description: The number of failure associations initiated by the local end

hwSctpGlobalStatAssocPassiveFail.name: hwSctpGlobalStatAssocPassiveFail
hwSctpGlobalStatAssocPassiveFail.description: The number of failure associations initiated by the remote end

hwSctpGlobalStatRecOotb.name: hwSctpGlobalStatRecOotb
hwSctpGlobalStatRecOotb.description: The number of received abnormal data chunks at the local end

hwSctpGlobalStatSendCtrlChunks.name: hwSctpGlobalStatSendCtrlChunks
hwSctpGlobalStatSendCtrlChunks.description: The number of transmitted control data chunks

hwSctpGlobalStatSendOrderChunks.name: hwSctpGlobalStatSendOrderChunks
hwSctpGlobalStatSendOrderChunks.description: The number of transmitted ordered data chunks

hwSctpGlobalStatSendUnorderChunks.name: hwSctpGlobalStatSendUnorderChunks
hwSctpGlobalStatSendUnorderChunks.description: The number of transmitted unordered data chunks

hwSctpGlobalStatRecCtrlChunks.name: hwSctpGlobalStatRecCtrlChunks
hwSctpGlobalStatRecCtrlChunks.description: The number of received control data chunks

hwSctpGlobalStatRecOrderChunks.name: hwSctpGlobalStatRecOrderChunks
hwSctpGlobalStatRecOrderChunks.description: The number of received ordered data chunks

hwSctpGlobalStatRecUnorderChunks.name: hwSctpGlobalStatRecUnorderChunks
hwSctpGlobalStatRecUnorderChunks.description: The number of received unordered data chunks

hwSctpGlobalStatRetransDataChunks.name: hwSctpGlobalStatRetransDataChunks
hwSctpGlobalStatRetransDataChunks.description: The number of retransmitted data chunks

hwSctpGlobalStatFragmentedUsrMsgs.name: hwSctpGlobalStatFragmentedUsrMsgs
hwSctpGlobalStatFragmentedUsrMsgs.description: The number of fragmented user messages

hwSctpGlobalStatReassembledUsrMsgs.name: hwSctpGlobalStatReassembledUsrMsgs
hwSctpGlobalStatReassembledUsrMsgs.description: The number of reassembled user messages

hwSctpGlobalStatChecksumErrors.name: hwSctpGlobalStatChecksumErrors
hwSctpGlobalStatChecksumErrors.description: The number of received checksum error packets

hwSctpGlobalStatSentSctpPacks.name: hwSctpGlobalStatSentSctpPacks
hwSctpGlobalStatSentSctpPacks.description: The number of the transmitted SCTP packets

hwSctpGlobalStatRecvSctpPacks.name: hwSctpGlobalStatRecvSctpPacks
hwSctpGlobalStatRecvSctpPacks.description: The number of the received SCTP packets

hwSctpGlobalStatAdminStatus.name: hwSctpGlobalStatAdminStatus
hwSctpGlobalStatAdminStatus.description: Clearing the system statistics. Options: 1. clear(1) -clear

hwSctpParaRtoMin.name: hwSctpParaRtoMin
hwSctpParaRtoMin.description: The minimum RTO. To the UA5000R15C05, this leaf can be read and written, the value range is (10..5000). To other products, this leaf just can be read, the default value is 1000. Unit: millisecond

hwSctpParaRtoMax.name: hwSctpParaRtoMax
hwSctpParaRtoMax.description: The maximum RTO. For Mg interface, default value 3000. For Iua-Link, default value 60000. To the UA5000R15C05, the value range is (200..120000). To other products, the value range is (3000..90000). Unit: millisecond

hwSctpParaRtoInit.name: hwSctpParaRtoInit
hwSctpParaRtoInit.description: The initial RTO. To the UA5000R15C05, the value range is (10..120000), the default value is 100. To other products, the value range is (1000..6000), the default value is 3000. Unit: millisecond

hwSctpParaValidCookieLife.name: hwSctpParaValidCookieLife
hwSctpParaValidCookieLife.description: Cookie lifecycle. To the UA5000R15C05, the value range is (5000..120000). To other products, the value range is (30000..120000). Default: 60000 Unit: millisecond

hwSctpParaMaxInitRetrans.name: hwSctpParaMaxInitRetrans
hwSctpParaMaxInitRetrans.description: The maximum retransmit attempts of INIT To the UA5000R15C05, the value range is (1..10). To other products, the value range is (3..10). Default: 6

hwSctpParaRtoAlpha.name: hwSctpParaRtoAlpha
hwSctpParaRtoAlpha.description: Parameter of RTO Alpha To the UA5000R15C05, the default value is 13, the value range is (1..100). To other products, the default value is 12, the value range is (0..100).

hwSctpParaRtoBeta.name: hwSctpParaRtoBeta
hwSctpParaRtoBeta.description: Parameter of RTO Beta To the UA5000R15C05, the value range is (1..100). To other products, the value range is (0..100). Default: 25

hwSctpParaAssocMaxRetrans.name: hwSctpParaAssocMaxRetrans
hwSctpParaAssocMaxRetrans.description: The maximum retransmit attempts in a association To the UA5000R15C05, the value range is (1..10), the default value is 8. To other products, the value range is (8..16), the default value is 10.

hwSctpParaPathMaxRetrans.name: hwSctpParaPathMaxRetrans
hwSctpParaPathMaxRetrans.description: The maximum Retransmit attempts in a path To the UA5000R15C05, the value range is (1..10), the default value is 8. To other products, the value range is (3..8), the default value is 5.

hwSctpParaNoCongestionLevel.name: hwSctpParaNoCongestionLevel
hwSctpParaNoCongestionLevel.description: Parameter of no-congestion level To the UA5000R15C05, the value range is (1..60). To other products, the value range is (0..60). Default: 40

hwSctpParaHbInterval.name: hwSctpParaHbInterval
hwSctpParaHbInterval.description: Heartbeat interval. To the UA5000R15C05, the value range is (1000..300000), the default value is 3000. To other products, the value range is (2000..120000), the default value is 30000. Unit: millisecond

hwSctpParaSendChecksum.name: hwSctpParaSendChecksum
hwSctpParaSendChecksum.description: Sending the checksum. Options: 1. no(1) -indicates that the checksum is not Sending 2. yes(2) -indicates that the checksum is Sending Default: 2

hwSctpParaRecvChecksum.name: hwSctpParaRecvChecksum
hwSctpParaRecvChecksum.description: Receiving the checksum. Options: 1. no(1) -indicates that the checksum is not Receiving 2. yes(2) -indicates that the checksum is Receiving Default: 2

hwSctpParaChecksumArith.name: hwSctpParaChecksumArith
hwSctpParaChecksumArith.description: Checksum algorithm. Options: 1. adler32(1) -indicates that Checksum algorithm is ADLER32 2. crc32(2) -indicates that Checksum algorithm is CRC32 Default: 2

hwIuaVersionString.name: hwIuaVersionString
hwIuaVersionString.description: The version of the L2UA protocol

hwSctpAssocInfoTable.name: hwSctpAssocInfoTable
hwSctpAssocInfoTable.description: This table is used to query infomation of a SCTP association. The index of this table is hwSctpAssocId.

hwSctpAssocInfoEntry.name: hwSctpAssocInfoEntry
hwSctpAssocInfoEntry.description: This table is used to query infomation of a SCTP association. The index of this entry is hwSctpAssocId.

hwSctpAssocId.name: hwSctpAssocId
hwSctpAssocId.description: SCTP association ID Constructed by Protocol-Type, MGC-index/Proxy-index, IUA-Link-ID/H248-Interface-ID/SIP-Interface-ID; Format:xyzzzzzz(Hex) a) x for Protocol-Type: IUA(0),H.248(1),SIP(2); b) y for MGC-index/Proxy-index: if x is IUA(0), y fixed to 0; if x is H.248(1), y for MGC index; if x is SIP(2), y for Proxy index; c) z for IUA-Link-ID/H248-Interface-ID/SIP-Interface-ID: if x is IUA(0), zzzzzz for IUA LinkNo; if x is H.248(1), zzzzzz for H248 interface ID; if x is SIP(2), zzzzzz for SIP interface ID;

hwSctpAssocState.name: hwSctpAssocState
hwSctpAssocState.description: Current status of the association Options: 1. closed(1) -indicates that the Current status of the association is closed 2. cookiewait(2) -indicates that the Current status of the association is down 3. cookieecho(3) -indicates that the Current status of the association is cookieecho 4. established(4) -indicates that the Current status of the association is established 5. shutdownpending(5) -indicates that the Current status of the association is shutdownpending 6. shutdownsent(6) -indicates that the Current status of the association is shutdownsent 7. shutdownreceived(7) -indicates that the Current status of the association is shutdownreceived 8. shutdownacksent(8) -indicates that the Current status of the association is shutdownacksent

hwSctpAssocType.name: hwSctpAssocType
hwSctpAssocType.description: Association type. Options: 1. client(1) -indicates that the Association type is Client 2. server(2) -indicates that the Association type is Server

hwSctpAssocLocalIPaddr.name: hwSctpAssocLocalIPaddr
hwSctpAssocLocalIPaddr.description: The current local primary IP address

hwSctpAssocRemoteIPaddr.name: hwSctpAssocRemoteIPaddr
hwSctpAssocRemoteIPaddr.description: The current remote primary IP address

hwSctpAssocAllowHB.name: hwSctpAssocAllowHB
hwSctpAssocAllowHB.description: Whether transmitting HB message. Options: 1. no(1) -indicates not transmitting HB message 2. yes(2) -indicates transmitting HB message Default: 2

hwSctpAssocLocalRwnd.name: hwSctpAssocLocalRwnd
hwSctpAssocLocalRwnd.description: The size of the local receiver window

hwSctpAssocRemoteRwnd.name: hwSctpAssocRemoteRwnd
hwSctpAssocRemoteRwnd.description: The size of the remote receiver window

hwSctpAssocUnfirmDataChunks.name: hwSctpAssocUnfirmDataChunks
hwSctpAssocUnfirmDataChunks.description: The size of the unacknowledged data that is transmitted

hwSctpAssocRemoteIP1State.name: hwSctpAssocRemoteIP1State
hwSctpAssocRemoteIP1State.description: The current status of remote IP address 1. Options: 1. active(1) -active 2. inactive(2) -inactive

hwSctpAssocRemoteIP1WaitAck.name: hwSctpAssocRemoteIP1WaitAck
hwSctpAssocRemoteIP1WaitAck.description: The number of the data blocks that is waiting for the acknowledgement by the remote SACK. Default: 2

hwSctpAssocRemoteIP1Cwnd.name: hwSctpAssocRemoteIP1Cwnd
hwSctpAssocRemoteIP1Cwnd.description: The size of the congestion window. Default: 2

hwSctpAssocRemoteIP1Unfirm.name: hwSctpAssocRemoteIP1Unfirm
hwSctpAssocRemoteIP1Unfirm.description: The size of the unacknowledged data that is transmitted on the path. Default: 2

hwSctpAssocRemoteIP1AllowHB.name: hwSctpAssocRemoteIP1AllowHB
hwSctpAssocRemoteIP1AllowHB.description: Whether HB can be transmitted from this address. Options: 1. no(1) -indicates that the HB can't be transmitted from this address 2. yes(2) -indicates that the HB can be transmitted from this address

hwSctpAssocRemoteIP2State.name: hwSctpAssocRemoteIP2State
hwSctpAssocRemoteIP2State.description: The current status of remote IP address 2 Options: 1. active(1) -indicates that the current status of remote IP address 2 is active 2. inactive(2) -indicates that the current status of remote IP address 2 is inactive

hwSctpAssocRemoteIP2WaitAck.name: hwSctpAssocRemoteIP2WaitAck
hwSctpAssocRemoteIP2WaitAck.description: The number of the data that is waiting for the acknowledgement by the remote SACK. -1 returns by GET means associate with IP2 does not exist. Default: 2

hwSctpAssocRemoteIP2Cwnd.name: hwSctpAssocRemoteIP2Cwnd
hwSctpAssocRemoteIP2Cwnd.description: The size of the congestion window. -1 returns by GET means associate with IP2 does not exist. Default: 2

hwSctpAssocRemoteIP2Unfirm.name: hwSctpAssocRemoteIP2Unfirm
hwSctpAssocRemoteIP2Unfirm.description: The size of the unacknowledged data that is transmitted on the path. -1 returns by GET means associate with IP2 does not exist. Default: 2

hwSctpAssocRemoteIP2Rto.name: hwSctpAssocRemoteIP2Rto
hwSctpAssocRemoteIP2Rto.description: Retransmission Time-out(ms) -1 returns by GET means associate with IP2 does not exist.

hwSctpAssocRemoteIP2Srtt.name: hwSctpAssocRemoteIP2Srtt
hwSctpAssocRemoteIP2Srtt.description: Smoothed Round-trip Time (ms) -1 returns by GET means associate with IP2 does not exist.

hwSctpAssocRemoteIP2Rttvar.name: hwSctpAssocRemoteIP2Rttvar
hwSctpAssocRemoteIP2Rttvar.description: Round-trip Time Variation (ms) -1 returns by GET means associate with IP2 does not exist.

hwSctpAssocRemoteIP2AllowHB.name: hwSctpAssocRemoteIP2AllowHB
hwSctpAssocRemoteIP2AllowHB.description: Whether HB can be sent from this address. Options: 1. no(1) -indicates that the HB can't be sent from this address 2. yes(2) -indicates that the HB can be sent from this address

hwIsdnIuaDuaErrStatsThresholdCfgTable.name: hwIsdnIuaDuaErrStatsThresholdCfgTable
hwIsdnIuaDuaErrStatsThresholdCfgTable.description: Configuration table of L2UA IUA/DUA link error statistic threshold. The index of this table is hwIsdnIuaDuaErrLinkNoIndex.

hwIsdnIuaDuaErrStatsThresholdCfgEntry.name: hwIsdnIuaDuaErrStatsThresholdCfgEntry
hwIsdnIuaDuaErrStatsThresholdCfgEntry.description: Configuration table of L2UA IUA/DUA link error statistic threshold. The index of this entry is hwIsdnIuaDuaErrLinkNoIndex.

hwMifSctpCfgParaTable.name: hwMifSctpCfgParaTable
